userdoc.notice: Script used to deploy a bedrock system. The entire system is deployed within the `run` function.         To add a new contract to the system, add a public function that deploys that individual contract.         Then add a call to that function inside of `run`. Be sure to call the `save` function after each         deployment so that hardhat-deploy style artifacts can be generated using a call to `sync()`.         The `CONTRACT_ADDRESSES_PATH` environment variable can be set to a path that contains a JSON file full of         contract name to address pairs. That enables this script to be much more flexible in the way it is used.         This contract must not have constructor logic because it is set into state using `etch`.
